  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variable font axis, including its tag, value range, default value, and visibility.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` holds the metadata for one axis of a variable font's fvar table. The
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Tag> identifies the axis (e.g., `wght` for weight),
while <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Min>, <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Default>,
and <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Max> define the allowed and default values.

Retrieve axes for a typeface using
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters(System.Span{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis})>.

`SKFontVariationAxis` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Axis: {axis.Tag}, Range: [{axis.Min}..{axis.Max}], Default: {axis.Default}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
